 stands: Case studies from jack pine in northern lower Michigan (2003) Forest Ecology and Management, 182 (1-3), pp. 247-257. , DOI 10.1016/S0378-1127(03)00049-5; Cotillas, M., Sabaté, S., Gràcia, C., Espelta, J.M., Growth response of mixed Mediterranean oak coppices to rainfall reduction: Could selective thinning have any influence on it? (2009) For Ecol Manage, 258, pp. 1677-1683; Fernández-Caldas, E., Tejedor, M., Quantin, P., (1985) Los Suelos Volcánicos de Canarias, p. 250. , Servicio de Publicaciones de la Universidad de La Laguna, la Laguna; Fernández-Palacios, J.M., De Nicolás, J.P., Altitudinal pattern of vegetation variation on Tenerife (1995) J Veg Sci, 6, pp. 183-190; Gea-Izquierdo, G., Martín-Benito, D., Cherubini, P., Cañellas, I., Climate-growth variability in Quercus ilex L. west Iberian open woodlands of different stand density (2009) Ann for Sci, 66, p. 802; Gieger, T., Leuschner, C., Altitudinal change in needle water relations of Pinus canariensis and possible evidence of a drought-induced alpine timberline on Mt. Teide, Tenerife (2004) Flora, 199 (2), pp. 100-109. , DOI 10.1078/0367-2530-00139; Grissino-Mayer, H.D., Evaluating crossdating accuracy: A manual and tutorial for the computer program COFECHA (2001) Tree-Ring Res, 57, pp. 205-221; (2007) Climate Change 2007: Synthesis Report, , IPCC Contribution of working groups I, II and III to the fourth assessment report of the intergovernmental panel on climate change CoreWriting Team, Pachauri RK, Reisinger A (eds). IPCC, Geneva, Switzerland; Jonsson, S., Gunnarson, B., Criado, C., Drought is the major limiting factor for tree-ring growth of high-altitude Canary Island Pines on Tenerife (2002) Geografiska Annaler, Series A: Physical Geography, 84 (1), pp. 51-71; Kohler, M., Sohn, J., Nägele, G., Bauhus, J., Can drought tolerance of Norway spruce (Picea abies (L.) Karst.) be increased through thinning? (2010) Eur J for Res, 129, pp. 1109-1118; Linares, J.C., Camarero, J.J., Carreira, J.A., Plastic responses of Abies pinsapo xylogenesis to drought and competition (2009) Tree Physiol, 29, pp. 1525-1536; Linares, J.C., Camarero, J.J., Carreira, J.A., Competition modulates the adaptation capacity of forests to climatic stress: Insights from recent growth decline and death in relict stands of the Mediterranean fir Abies pinsapo (2010) J Ecol, 98, pp. 592-603; Madrigal, A., Domínguez, M.L., Peraza, M., Barber, J.R., Herrero, J., Rodríguez-Solano, R., (1989) Estudio de la Selvicultura de Las Masa Artificiales de Pinus Canariensis Sweet Ex Spreng, , Gobierno de Canarias Dirección General del Medio Ambiente; Fundación General de la Universidad Politécnica de Madrid Departamento de Silvopascicultura Santa Cruz de Tenerife y Madrid; Makinen, H., Isomaki, A., Thinning intensity and long-term changes in increment and stem form of Scots pine trees (2004) Forest Ecology and Management, 203 (1-3), pp. 21-34. , DOI 10.1016/j.foreco.2004.07.028, PII S0378112704005481; Martín-Benito, D., Cherubini, P., Del Río, M., Cañellas, I., Growth response to climate and drought in Pinus nigra Arn. trees of different crown classes (2008) Trees, 22, pp. 363-373; Martín-Benito, D., Del Río, M., Heinrich, H., Helle, G., Cañellas, I., Response of climate-growth relationships and water use efficiency to thinning in a Pinus nigra afforestation (2010) For Ecol Manage, 259, pp. 967-975; Mason, S.J., Mimmack, G.M., The use of bootstrap confidence intervals for the correlation coefficient in climatology (1992) Theor Appl Climatol, 45, pp. 229-233; McDowell, N., Brooks, J.R., Fitzgerald, S.A., Bond, B.J., Carbon isotope discrimination and growth response of old Pinus ponderosa trees to stand density reductions (2003) Plant, Cell and Environment, 26 (4), pp. 631-644. , DOI 10.1046/j.1365-3040.2003.00999.x; Misson, L., Nicault, A., Guiot, J., Effects of different thinning intensities on drought response in Norway spruce (Picea abies (L.) Karst.) (2003) For Ecol Manage, 183, pp. 47-60; Moreno, G., Cube